# Production Environment Configuration
# DO NOT commit this file with real credentials
# All values should be environment variables or AWS Secrets Manager

# Note: In production, this file should NOT be used
# Instead, set environment variables in your deployment:
# - ECS Task Definition
# - Lambda environment variables
# - Docker environment variables
# - Kubernetes ConfigMap/Secret

# Example production environment variables:
# ENV=production
# LOG_LEVEL=error
# SERVER_PORT=8080
# SERVER_TIMEOUT=90
# ENABLE_SWAGGER=false
# AWS_REGION=us-east-1
# AWS_SECRETS_NAME=go-starter-prod-secrets

# Production Deployment Checklist:
# ✓ Secrets Manager: go-starter-prod-secrets
#   - database_url: postgresql://user:password@prod-db-cluster.rds.amazonaws.com:5432/go_starter_prod
#   - api_keys: sensitive data
#   - encryption_keys: if needed

# ✓ IAM Roles configured:
#   - Task execution role (for ECR, CloudWatch)
#   - Task role (for Secrets Manager, S3, DynamoDB)

# ✓ ECS Fargate configuration:
#   - CPU: 512-1024 (based on load)
#   - Memory: 1024-2048 MB
#   - Log retention: 30 days
#   - Health check: /api/v1/health

# ✓ Auto-scaling:
#   - Min: 2 instances
#   - Max: 10+ instances
#   - Target CPU: 70%
#   - Target Memory: 80%

# ✓ Load Balancer:
#   - ALB with HTTPS (TLS 1.2+)
#   - Health check: /api/v1/health (30s interval, 5s timeout)
#   - Stickiness: disabled

# ✓ Monitoring & Alerts:
#   - CloudWatch dashboards
#   - Error rate > 5%
#   - Response time > 2000ms
#   - CPU/Memory > 85%

# ✓ Logging:
#   - CloudWatch Logs: /ecs/go-starter-prod
#   - Log retention: 30 days
#   - JSON structured logging enabled

# ✓ CI/CD Pipeline:
#   - Build: GitHub Actions
#   - Test: Unit + integration tests
#   - Security scan: CodeBuild
#   - ECR push: Latest + version tags
#   - ECS deployment: Blue-green or rolling

# ✓ Database:
#   - RDS Multi-AZ enabled
#   - Automated backups: 30 days
#   - Read replicas for scaling
#   - Encryption at rest enabled

# ✓ Security:
#   - VPC with private subnets
#   - Security groups: minimal permissions
#   - WAF: enabled (optional)
#   - DDoS protection: Shield (if on AWS)
#   - Secrets rotation: enabled
